sections.heading: Defects; when considered waived
sections.text: The accused shall be taken to have waived all defects which may be excepted to by a motion to quash, or a plea in abatement, by demurring to an indictment or pleading in bar or the general issue.SourceG.S.1873, c. 58, ยง 444, p. 822;R.S.1913, ยง 9088;C.S.1922, ยง 10113;C
